===Etymology===
From {{uder|en|tr|yaşmak}}.<ref>[http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/yashmak "yashmak."] ''Merriam-Webster Online Dictionary.'' Merriam-Webster. 2008.</ref>
===Pronunciation===
* {{hyphenation|en|yash|mak}}
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A [[veil]] worn by [[Muslim]] women to cover parts of the face when they are in public.
#* '''1982''', {{w|TC Boyle}}, ''Water Music'', Penguin 2006, p. 46:
#*: Mungo cannot make out her face, which is concealed behind a '''''yashmak''''' – the double horsehair veil worn by Muslim women in public – but he is immediately struck by her feet and hands.
====Synonyms====
* {{sense|veil that covers parts of the face}} {{l|en|niqab}}, {{l|en|veil}}, {{l|en|hijab}}, {{l|en|purdah}}, {{l|en|scarf}}
